I find these errors annoying as well.

If I am not mistaken this addition of the route to the interface's net is done already in netinet/in.c:1581 (12.3) :


        /*
         * Add route for the network.
         */
        if (vhid == 0) {
                int flags = RTF_UP;

                if (ifp->if_flags & (IFF_LOOPBACK|IFF_POINTOPOINT))
                        flags |= RTF_HOST;

                error = in_addprefix(ia, flags);
                if (error)
                        goto fail1;
        }

So, the addition of _loopback for the inet and inet6 case can be removed IMHO.

Adding melifaro to CC:. He made changes in in.c related to this (https://reviews.freebsd.org/D28246) handling PR #252883
